“proper layer”; the thin, supporting CT layer underlying all epithelia

In bronchioles, cartilage and glands are absent.
A large bronchiole has a typical respiratory epithelium (E) and prominent smooth muscle (SM). The walls are supported by fibrous CT.
Note: As bronchioles luminal diameter decreases their epithelium changes to ciliated cuboidal and their walls become dominated by several layers of smooth muscle.
